l},{"id":3569124,"name":"Andy Gasser","username":"gdefender","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/gdefender/{size}/168507_2.png","created_at":"2025-03-26T15:55:31.897Z","cooked":"<p>There’s a great article in the WPILib documentation about tuning an elevator with motion profiling, including a simulation, in the WPILib documentation: <a href="https://docs.wpilib.org/en/stable/docs/software/advanced-controls/introduction/tuning-elevator.html" class="inline-onebox" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">Tuning a Vertical Elevator with Motion Profiling — FIRST Robotics Competition documentation</a></p>
<p>You can certainly try to use SysID or reCalc to calculate gain values, but manual tuning is often simpler and good enough for <span class="abbreviation">FRC<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="FIRST Robotics Competition"></template></span>. The document above has a good simulation with a recommended procedure <a href="https://docs.wpilib.org/en/stable/docs/software/advanced-controls/introduction/tuning-elevator.html#motion-profiled-feedforward-and-feedback-control" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">here</a>.</p>
<p>I recommend using Tuner X to tune the values on the fly, it’s a super useful tool. You can change the values and configure the controllers immediately. Then you can put position and velocity on the graph, and even run the motor. Once you get it working well in Tuner X, I’d take the gain values and move them into the code.</p>","post_number":6,"post_type":1,"posts_count":9,"updated_at":"2025-03-26T15:55:31.897Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":5,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":3,"reads":80,"readers_count":79,"score":36.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":496908,"topic_slug":"struggles-with-using-magic-motion-for-kraken-motor","display_username":"Andy Gasser","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://docs.wpilib.org/en/stable/docs/software/advanced-controls/introduction/tuning-elevator.html","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"Tuning a Vertical Elevator with Motion Profiling — FIRST Robotics Competition documentation","clicks":4},{"url":"https://docs.wpilib.org/en/stable/docs/software/advanced-controls/introduction/tuning-elevator.html#motion-profiled-feedforward-and-feedback-control","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"Tuning a Vertical Elevator with Motion Profiling — FIRST Robotics Competition documentation","clicks":4}],"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":69420,"username":"chereshenka","name":"Angelina","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/chereshenka/{size}/264148_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":44380,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"7028 - Java Programming Mentor"}